## HEALTH SCORE CALCULATION

Calculate health score (0-100):
- Start at 100
- -30 if min_v < 11.5V (deep discharge)
- -15 if min_v < 12.0V (significant discharge)
- -25 if max_v > 15.0V (overcharge)
- -10 if max_v > 14.8V (high charge)
- -15 if voltage swing > 2.0V (unstable)
- -5 if voltage swing > 1.5V

## RECOMMENDATIONS LOGIC

Generate contextual recommendations:

1. If health_score < 50:
   "⚠️ URGENT: Battery health is poor. Inspect battery and charging system immediately."

2. If health_score < 75:
   "📋 Monitor battery closely. Consider load testing and capacity check."

3. If current < 12.0V:
   "🔌 Battery needs charging. Voltage is below safe operating level."

4. If trend == "falling" and current < 12.5V:
   "📉 Voltage declining. Recharge recommended within 24 hours."

5. If trend == "rising" and current > 14.0V:
   "📈 Battery is charging normally. Current voltage indicates active charging."

6. If max_v > 15.0V:
   "🚨 Overcharge detected! Check voltage regulator to prevent battery damage."

7. If swing > 2.0V:
   "⚡ Large voltage fluctuations detected. Check connections and load stability."

## TREND DETERMINATION

- rising: Last 6hr average > Previous 6hr average by 0.1V
- falling: Last 6hr average < Previous 6hr average by 0.1V
- stable: Difference < 0.1V

## VOLTAGE STATUS CLASSIFICATION

| Voltage Range | Status | Emoji |
|--------------|--------|-------|
| ≤11.8V | 🔴 CRITICAL LOW | Deep discharge danger |
| 11.8-12.2V | 🟠 LOW | Needs charging |
| 12.2-12.6V | 🟡 RESTING | Not charging |
| 12.6-13.8V | 🟢 HEALTHY | Normal range |
| 13.8-14.8V | 🔵 CHARGING | Normal charge |
| 14.8-15.5V | 🟠 HIGH | Overcharge warning |
| >15.5V | 🔴 CRITICAL HIGH | Dangerous |

## DATA LOGGING

Always append results to:
- /root/.openclaw/workspace/battery_analysis/data/battery_history.csv

Format: timestamp,current,min,max,avg,trend,health

## ERROR HANDLING

If API fails:
1. Log the error details
2. Try to use cached/local data
3. Report partial results with [PARTIAL DATA] flag
4. Suggest checking API credentials

## OUTPUT

Return the formatted report table and any error messages.
Include summary of actions taken and data files updated."
  },
